value.0: "Right then, thanks for the help. Stop by the Pawnshop later. I think you'll be pleased." Stiletto grins at you before slipping past you and into the shadows beyond.
"So you came back. Is there a reason, or do you just enjoy watching others suffer?" The halfling offers you a morbid wink.
A halfling prisoner stands whistling in his cell, seemingly oblivious to all that is going on around him. Then he looks up at you and gives you a roguish grin.
"Have you come to poke a sharp stick in me then, or are you more of a curiosity seeker?"
"I'll just wait here then. No rush, but if you'd care to open the door, I'd be happy to vacate the cell for someone else."
"Aye, I should've known. Don't suppose there is anything I could do to change your mind?"
"I promise that if you free me, I will leave a nice gift for ya at the Pawnshop. That's the best I can do, since the Hand and her guards stripped me of everything they could find."
"I was exhausted by my regular job as a free person, so I thought I'd just hop into a prison cell and take a much needed break!"
"Wait... wait, I'm sorry about that. I'll try to be more serious now, though I doubt I'll succeed."
"Good point. Sorry about that. I'll try to be more serious, though I doubt I'll succeed."
"Ha, ha! I like ya, funny <man/woman>. Alright then, I'll try to be serious. I doubt I'll succeed though."
"I was relatively new in town and I saw this woman who looked like she needed a break from the heavy load in her purse."
"Naturally, the gentleman in me decided I should give her a hand. No sooner had I slipped my knife into her purse strings, then I found myself on the ground with my arm trapped behind my back."
"It turns out that the fancy lady I was trying to rob was Enivid, the Hand, captain of the guards and head of the military. I just thought it was some showy armor!"

"Apparently she isn't terribly fond of thieves, and even less fond of ones that try to steal from her. So here I sit, feeling terribly remorseful and full of self-loathing, wishing I could make amends."
His eyes grow large and soulful. "Oh yes, m'<lord/lady>. I would do anything to be free of here... I mean free of my sordid past."
"I would rather not. If you get the chance, speak to Southpaw. He'd vouch for me, I'm sure, and he's a respected member of the community."
"Ah, well... enjoy your killing spree. If ya get bored, I can offer you a little something to set me free."
"My name is Stiletto. And you would be?"
"Right. Should have seen that one coming. Try to keep a smile up in here, and what good does it do you? What do you want then?"
"Well, that would be bloody decent of you. Just pop that door open and I'll be on my way."
"Well, I'm not going anywhere, unless the Hand decides to hang me. Still, I'd rather ya didn't take to long."
"If that be the same key that opens the other prison doors, it won't help me, I'm afraid. This is a special cell, where the Hand can lock up her own personal prisoners."
"I am afraid I did something to upset the higher authorities. I'm in a fair bit of trouble, so if you could just find a way for me to get out, I'd be much obliged."
"You seem to have gotten yourself into some serious trouble."

"The milk of human compassion not good enough for ya? I guess not. I haven't a thing on me, but if you let me go, I'll leave a nice little gift for ya with the master of the thieves guild at the pawnshop."
"You don't, now do ya? But if ya kill me you get nothing. If ya set me free, ya have a chance that it'll work out in your favor. What have ya got to lose?"
The halfling grimaces, then shrugs and decides to ignore you.

value.0: "I have some lock picks."
"Goodbye."
"I was just looking for something to kill."
"I'll have to think about it."
"No, thanks. I just like killing."
"Any reward if I set you free?"
"Like what?"
"What are you doing in there?"
"I'll just let you get back to your rest then."
"Do you usually insult people who might be able to free you?"
"I know I look like I should have a sense of humor, but I don't."
"Seriously, why are you in prison?"
"Who caught you?"
"What happened?"
"I think I'll kill you now."
"You can just stay in here and rot, for all I care."
"Are you truly repentant of your crime?"
"I don't believe you. You will have to stay here."
"I was killing the enemy captives who escaped their cells."
"Who are you?"
"I'll ask the questions here."
"Would you like me to let you out?"
"I'm here to rescue you."
"No, I changed my mind."
"Hang in there, I'll be back."
"I have the key right here. Just a second."
"What did you do?"
"Not so fast. Is there a reward you can offer me?"
"How do I know I can trust you?"
"I want the simple pleasure of killing you."
"How do I get it open?"
"I have other questions."
"Is there any other way?"
"I'll go get some."
